3
00:00:45,500 --> 00:00:52,560
(Paramount)

4
00:00:52,560 --> 00:00:53,480
The Commander is here.

5
00:00:53,480 --> 00:00:54,340
Commander.

6
00:00:55,950 --> 00:00:56,539
Commander.

7
00:00:56,540 --> 00:00:57,619
Commander, over here.

8
00:00:57,620 --> 00:00:59,160
- Look this way.
- Commander, over here.

9
00:01:02,630 --> 00:01:03,830
It's the Commander's wife.

10
00:01:04,620 --> 00:01:05,890
She's gorgeous.

11
00:01:07,820 --> 00:01:09,399
- Madam, look over here.
- Madam.

12
00:01:09,400 --> 00:01:11,140
- Over here.
- This way.

13
00:01:12,380 --> 00:01:13,260
Madam.

14
00:01:14,230 --> 00:01:16,079
Commander, look this way.

15
00:01:16,080 --> 00:01:16,910
Madam.

16
00:01:19,580 --> 00:01:20,770
Madam, over here.

17
00:01:24,030 --> 00:01:25,830
♪Night Shanghai♪

18
00:01:26,070 --> 00:01:27,830
♪Night Shanghai♪

19
00:01:28,030 --> 00:01:31,860
♪You are a sleepless city♪

20
00:01:32,010 --> 00:01:34,109
♪The lights glow bright♪

21
00:01:34,110 --> 00:01:35,970
- ♪The traffic hums♪
- Commander.

22
00:01:36,270 --> 00:01:39,400
♪Songs and dancing fill the night♪

23
00:01:40,290 --> 00:01:42,099
♪All you see♪

24
00:01:42,100 --> 00:01:44,010
♪Are smiling faces♪

25
00:01:46,040 --> 00:01:48,270
Commander.

26
00:01:49,320 --> 00:01:49,819
Commander.

27
00:01:49,820 --> 00:01:50,539
You're here too?

28
00:01:51,520 --> 00:01:52,479
Boss Huang.

29
00:01:52,480 --> 00:01:54,269
Enjoy yourselves. We'll head over first.

30
00:01:54,270 --> 00:01:55,000
Alright.

31
00:02:00,000 --> 00:02:02,419
This is where Yancheng's
businessmen gather.

32
00:02:02,420 --> 00:02:04,080
If you want to expand your connections,

33
00:02:04,080 --> 00:02:07,619
Paramount is the best place
to gather information.

34
00:02:07,620 --> 00:02:08,660
Thank you.

35
00:02:10,630 --> 00:02:15,079
♪Drowsy eyes in the hazy dawn♪

36
00:02:15,080 --> 00:02:17,869
♪Everyone heads home with weary hearts♪

37
00:02:17,870 --> 00:02:22,420
♪Following the turning wheels♪

38
00:02:22,740 --> 00:02:23,139
Come on.

39
00:02:23,140 --> 00:02:26,760
♪Entering a brand new world♪

40
00:02:26,980 --> 00:02:30,830
♪A whole new life awaits♪

41
00:02:31,800 --> 00:02:33,760
Commander, it's been a long time.

42
00:02:33,760 --> 00:02:34,599
Chairman Lin.

43
00:02:34,600 --> 00:02:36,360
(Lin Li, Chairman of
the Yancheng Chamber of Commerce)

44
00:02:36,360 --> 00:02:38,120
This must be your wife.

45
00:02:38,860 --> 00:02:39,699
Chairman Lin.

46
00:02:39,700 --> 00:02:40,460
Hello.

47
00:02:41,300 --> 00:02:42,259
This is my daughter.

48
00:02:42,260 --> 00:02:43,379
Greetings, Commander.

49
00:02:43,380 --> 00:02:44,219
Commander.

50
00:02:44,220 --> 00:02:44,939
Greetings, Madam.

51
00:02:44,940 --> 00:02:46,020
Madam.

52
00:02:46,660 --> 00:02:49,220
I've always wondered
what kind of woman you married.

53
00:02:49,580 --> 00:02:52,220
Now that I've met her,
she truly is elegant and extraordinary.

54
00:02:52,940 --> 00:02:53,939
You're too kind.

55
00:02:53,940 --> 00:02:58,060
I heard you studied in France.

56
00:02:58,140 --> 00:02:59,100
What a coincidence.

57
00:02:59,460 --> 00:03:00,460
I happen to know

58
00:03:00,700 --> 00:03:01,699
some French too.

59
00:03:01,700 --> 00:03:04,460
Perhaps we can
speak French together sometime.

60
00:03:07,500 --> 00:03:10,019
I'd like that. But it's been a long time
since I've spoken French.

61
00:03:10,020 --> 00:03:11,139
I'm a bit rusty.

62
00:03:11,140 --> 00:03:13,139
I hope there'll be more opportunities

63
00:03:13,140 --> 00:03:14,980
to speak with you, Mr. Lin.

64
00:03:16,860 --> 00:03:17,659
Commander.

65
00:03:17,660 --> 00:03:20,339
You truly married
a beautiful, intelligent,

66
00:03:20,340 --> 00:03:22,100
and graceful wife.

67
00:03:22,660 --> 00:03:23,860
I'm quite envious.

68
00:03:24,500 --> 00:03:25,580
You're flattering her.

69
00:03:26,300 --> 00:03:26,699
Madam,

70
00:03:26,700 --> 00:03:29,379
I heard you play the piano beautifully.

71
00:03:29,380 --> 00:03:31,100
Would you honor us with a performance

72
00:03:31,220 --> 00:03:33,380
and let us enjoy it?

73
00:03:34,820 --> 00:03:36,220
You play piano too?

74
00:03:37,420 --> 00:03:39,179
It's not as impressive as Mr. Lin says.

75
00:03:39,180 --> 00:03:40,619
I only know the basics.

76
00:03:40,620 --> 00:03:42,340
It's hardly worthy of an audience.

77
00:03:42,740 --> 00:03:43,699
You're too modest.

78
00:03:43,700 --> 00:03:46,180
- If you don't feel like playing...
- I'll play instead.

79
00:03:46,580 --> 00:03:47,540
Good. Good.

80
00:03:47,900 --> 00:03:48,900
Please.

81
00:03:55,340 --> 00:03:56,339
Commander.

82
00:03:56,340 --> 00:03:57,740
I thought after getting married,

83
00:03:57,780 --> 00:03:59,259
you wouldn't have time for me anymore.

84
00:03:59,260 --> 00:04:00,259
(Lily)

85
00:04:00,260 --> 00:04:02,060
Isn't Lily still

86
00:04:02,460 --> 00:04:04,060
the one who understands you best?

87
00:04:08,740 --> 00:04:10,100
Without my permission,

88
00:04:10,620 --> 00:04:12,480
don't come to the residence
looking for me again.

89
00:04:12,940 --> 00:04:13,860
Understood?

90
00:04:16,060 --> 00:04:17,220
Why not?

91
00:04:38,420 --> 00:04:39,950
That was wonderful.

92
00:05:33,140 --> 00:05:33,980
Commander.

93
00:05:34,220 --> 00:05:34,979
He's here too.

94
00:05:34,980 --> 00:05:35,419
We...

95
00:05:35,420 --> 00:05:37,539
(Lieutenant Li, Gu Nianchi's lieutenant)

96
00:05:37,540 --> 00:05:38,420
Keep it down.

97
00:05:40,780 --> 00:05:42,900
Go get the Commander's
uniform from the cabinet.

98
00:05:43,180 --> 00:05:44,020
Alright.

99
00:05:50,180 --> 00:05:50,940
Chairman Lin,

100
00:05:52,140 --> 00:05:53,840
about that last shipment
of military supplies,

101
00:05:53,840 --> 00:05:55,720
I'd still like to discuss it
with you privately.

102
00:05:56,260 --> 00:05:57,740
Of course.

103
00:06:10,420 --> 00:06:14,899
♪How can broken love ever go on?♪

104
00:06:14,900 --> 00:06:17,340
Even with your eyes like this,
you still roasted chicken for me.

105
00:06:17,700 --> 00:06:18,460
How about this?

106
00:06:18,660 --> 00:06:19,940
I'll sing you a song instead.

107
00:06:21,340 --> 00:06:21,940
Alright.

108
00:06:22,130 --> 00:06:25,790
♪In the blink of an eye,
everything falls apart♪

109
00:06:26,090 --> 00:06:29,220
♪Bound by the fate we cannot escape♪

110
00:06:29,260 --> 00:06:34,370
♪You and I caught in
this tangled love and hate♪

111
00:06:35,470 --> 00:06:40,570
♪Fragile hearts can hardly bear goodbye♪

112
00:06:41,820 --> 00:06:47,350
♪How many times
must pain cut deep before we wake?♪

113
00:06:47,510 --> 00:06:51,420
♪I once gave myself
to you so completely♪

114
00:06:51,460 --> 00:06:54,479
♪Still holding on to that heart♪

115
00:06:54,480 --> 00:06:58,739
♪Only to suffer your fatal blow♪

116
00:06:58,740 --> 00:07:01,580
Let's step aside and talk business.

117
00:07:02,820 --> 00:07:03,500
Please.

118
00:07:03,680 --> 00:07:04,089
Please.

119
00:07:04,090 --> 00:07:06,669
♪Yet I approach you with such caution♪

120
00:07:06,670 --> 00:07:08,719
♪How could a stand in ever have♪

121
